CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1945, pg. 26 reads: "Nuptials - Charming gathering at the wedding of the former Florence Williams and W. James Adams. The ceremony was performed at the home of the bride's parents, Mr. and Mrs. J. V. Williams, 2429 Waring Court, Terrace Village II.  Left to right :Jack Cooper, the groom, W. James Adams; the bride, Florence Williams; maid of honor, Mrs. Lou Williams; J. V. Williams, brother of the bride. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of J. V. Williams, and seven women, including bride Florence Williams Adams seated center, and Mrs. Lou Williams seated right, posed in Williams home, 2429 Waring Court, Terrace Village II
